  "paper_analysis": {
    "summary": "This paper studies the crystal structures and Raman-active lattice vibrations of the magnetic topological insulator series MnBi2Te4·n(Bi2Te3) for n = 0 to 6, including newly characterized high-n members n = 4, 5, and 6. X-ray powder diffraction and Rietveld/Le Bail analysis establish the structures, while confocal Raman spectroscopy shows that for n > 0 the observed Raman modes are dominated by quintuple-layer Bi2Te3-like vibrations rather than the full site-symmetry mode count expected from the unit cell.",
